#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/cron-guide.xml:272
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want users other than root to have access to the cron daemon, you'll\n"
"want to read this section, otherwise, you can proceed to the next section, <uri\n"
"link=\"#scheduling\">scheduling cron-jobs</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
"root以外のユーザをcronデーモンにアクセスできるようにしたいなら、この章を読んでください。\n"
"そうでなければ、次の章である<uri link=\"#scheduling\">cronジョブの登録</uri>に進みましょう。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/cron-guide.xml:278
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Giving another user access to crontab does not let him run cron-jobs as root.\n"
"If you want a user to be able to edit the root crontab, you should look into\n"
"<c>sudo</c>. Please read our <uri link=\"/doc/en/sudo-guide.xml\">Gentoo\n"
"Sudo(ers) Guide</uri> for more details.\n"
msgstr ""
"他のユーザにcrontabの利用を許可するということは、cronジョブをrootとして実行できるようにすることではありません。\n"
"ユーザがrootのcrontabを編集できるようにしたいなら、<c>sudo</c>を検討すべきです。\n"
"詳細は<uri link=\"/doc/en/sudo-guide.xml\">Gentoo Sudo(ers) Guide</uri><uri link=\"/doc/ja/sudo-guide.xml\">(日本語訳)</uri>を参照してください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/cron-guide.xml:285
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"No matter which cron package you use, if you want to allow a user to use\n"
"crontab, he will first have to be in the cron group. As an example, if you\n"
"wanted to add the user <e>wepy</e> to the cron group you would run:\n"
msgstr ""
